FBIS3-13918 "drnes055_m_94011" FBIS-NES-94-055 Document Type:Daily Report 20 Mar 1994 JORDAN King Visits Wounded From Hebron Massacre JN2003203494 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1800 GMT 20 Mar 94 JN2003203494 Amman Jordan Television Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] His Majesty King Husayn this evening visited the wounded victims from the Holy Ibrahimi Mosque's massacre, who are receiving medical treatment at the al-Husayn Medical Center in Amman and reassured himself about their condition and the treatment they receive from their brothers in this esteemed medical establishment. The wounded patients expressed thanks and appreciation to His Majesty King Husayn for his generous Hashemite initiative toward the victims of the ugly massacre, committed in the holy Ibrahimi Mosque during the blessed month of Ramadan, and Jordan's honorable pan-Arab position, under the leadership of his majesty in support of their brothers the sons of the Palestinian people and the holy shrines in all circumstances. His Majesty King Husayn had ordered the formation of a higher committee to raise donations for the massacre's victims. His majesty donated a sum of 100,000 dinars for the victims, and ordered that everything possible be provided to assist the wounded in Jordanian hospitals. King Husayn was accompanied by His Highness Prince Hamzah Bin-al-Husayn, and al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir, Royal Hashemite Court chief.
